83.5	A_Million_Little_Pieces	A Million Little Pieces	A Million Little Pieces is a semi-fictional memoir by James Frey. It tells the story of a 23-year-old alcoholic and drug abuser and how he copes with rehabilitation in a Twelve steps-oriented treatment center. While initially promoted as a memoir, it was later discovered that many of the events described in the book never happened.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/3/37/A_Million_Little_Pieces.jpg
